definitions.definition: A vector quantity that denotes the rate of change of position with respect to time, combining speed with a directional component.
examples: A car racing in a circle may retain the same speed while continually changing its velocity .
The train was travelling at a slower velocity than usual.

definitions.definition: The number of times that an average unit of currency is spent during a specific period of time.
